sentences: As an engineer on Yebba's Dawn, he was nominated for the Grammy Award for Best Engineered Album, Non-Classical at the 64th Annual Grammy Awards.
Brenneck ran a small recording studio out of his home in Bushwick, Brooklyn before opening Dunham Sound Studios with Homer Steinwiess in Williamsburg in 2008.
section: == History == | === Dunham Records and recording studios ===

sentences: In 2014, the studio was succeeded by The Diamond Mine, a recording studio in Long Island City founded with Steinweiss, Nick Movshon, and Leon Michels.
section: == History == | === Dunham Records and recording studios ===

sentences: In 2017, Brenneck moved to Los Angeles with his wife and two children.
section: == History == | === Dunham Records and recording studios ===

sentences: He now works out of Los Angeles' The Sound Factory studio with Mark Ronson, whom he got to know well during his time with Winehouse.
